{"name": "poorkit", "metadata": {"name": "poorkit", "version": "0.0.4", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": "https://github.com/huxulm/poorkit", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["click"], "summary": "A programmer's personal tool collection.", "upload_time": 1733136068}, "documentation": ["# Poorkit\n\nA programmer's personal tool collection. It provides a set of utilities and helpers to make common tasks easier and more efficient.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Lightweight**: Minimal dependencies to keep your project lean.\n- **Easy to Use**: Simple and intuitive API.\n- **Extensible**: Easily add your own utilities and helpers.\n\n## Installation\n\nTo install Poorkit, use pip:\n\n```bash\npip install poorkit\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nHere is a basic example of how to use Poorkit:\n\n```shell\npk file create --name \"README.md\" --content \"Hi, poorkit!\"\n```\n\n## Contributing\n\nWe welcome contributions! Please read our [contributing guidelines](CONTRIBUTING.md) for more details.\n\n## License\n\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License. See the [LICENSE](LICENSE) file for details.\n\n## Contact\n\nFor any questions or feedback, please open an issue on GitHub.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "poorkit", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "poorkit.cli", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "poorkit.version", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "poorkit.help", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "file", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "file.file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params